ople, but also the limits of ethical policing, the authority of experts, and the nature of sexual difference itself—debates that had often unexpected effects on the gay community’s rights and freedoms. Examining those battles, Vice Patrol enriches understandings of the regulation of queer life in the twentieth century and disputes about police power that continue today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aGays-Legal status, laws, etc.-United States. 0aLaw enforcementxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aLaw enforcementzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLaw enforcement-United States-History-20th century. 0aMale homosexualityxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aMale homosexualityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMale homosexuality-United States-History-20th century. 0aVice controlxHistoryy20th centuryzUnited States. 0aVice controlzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aVice control-United States-History-20th century. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  apolice, vice squads, liquor laws, entrapment, clandestine surveillance, homosexuality, gay bars, courts, expertise, public knowledge.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishz978311075409408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021z9783110753868oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226769813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226769813/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2